{
  "texts": [
    "These findings match the ones observed for AI-focused strategy understanding (Colin et al., 2022; Fel et al., 2023).",
    "Given that saliency maps rarely improved human image classification performance, one might wonder whether they are more helpful in other tasks.",
    "One study examined their potential to support experienced chess players in selecting their moves (Puri et al., 2019).",
    "A particular type of saliency map indeed was helpful, while two others even impaired performance.",
    "Still, this partial benefit might be instructive as it reflects an instance where the capabilities of saliency maps matched the specific task requirements."
  ]
}